description: The Exponential class defines three easing functions to implement motion with Flex effect classes, where the motion is defined by an exponentially decaying sine wave.  For more information, see http://www.robertpenner.com/profmx.

members.description: The easeIn() method starts motion slowly, and then accelerates motion as it executes.

values: b Specifies the initial position of a component.
c Specifies the total change in position of the component.
d Specifies the duration of the effect, in milliseconds.
Number corresponding to the position of the component.

members.description: The easeOut() method starts motion fast, and then decelerates motion as it executes.

values: b Specifies the initial position of a component.
c Specifies the total change in position of the component.
d Specifies the duration of the effect, in milliseconds.
Number corresponding to the position of the component.

members.description: The easeInOut() method combines the motion of the easeIn() and easeOut() methods to start the motion slowly, accelerate motion, then decelerate.

values: b Specifies the initial position of a component.
c Specifies the total change in position of the component.
d Specifies the duration of the effect, in milliseconds.
Number corresponding to the position of the component.
